en: Broken and repaired, with some pieces missing, most from the black areas of the body but also a large section of the main scene, including the legs, chest, and neck of Theseus; the face, right leg, and right shoulder and arm of the Minotaur; and the right leg of one spectator. Details in added red are well preserved, but most added white has been lost. All previous repainting has been removed.
In red wash on the bottom of the foot, now quite pale, a ligature, possibly *P*R.
Fogg Art Museum Acquisitions 1962-1963 (before cleaning); Buitron 1972, 32-33, no. 12.
